Package: rpptx
Title: Create, Read, and Update PowerPoint Presentations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Mark", "Heckmann", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "heckmann.mark@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0736-7417"))
Description: Create, read, and update PowerPoint (.pptx) files. An R port of
    the Python 'python-pptx' library. Provides an R6-based object model for
    manipulating presentations, slides, shapes, text, charts, tables, and
    formatting properties. Supports autoshapes, text boxes, pictures, tables,
    charts (column, bar, line, pie, scatter, bubble, radar, doughnut), fills,
    lines, colors, freeform custom-geometry shapes, and placeholder inheritance.
URL: https://github.com/markheckmann/rpptx
BugReports: https://github.com/markheckmann/rpptx/issues
